				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ Ra=\frac{g\ast {\beta}_a\ast {\rho}_a\ast \left({T}_c-{T}_a\right)\ast {l_r}^3}{\alpha_a\ast {\mu}_a} $$\end{document}

The volumetric thermal expansion coefficient of air is a function of the average value of water and the surrounding air temperatures Tf (K) while the value of thermal diffusivity of air αa depends on the thermal conductivity of air Ka (W/m K), air density ρa (Kg/m3), and the specific heat of air Cpa (kJ/kg .K)
13αa=Kaρa∗Cpa\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
